.TH NODEX 1 "2026-07-13" "nodex 0.1.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
nodex \- secure CLI for inspecting and operating self\-hosted infrastructure
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B nodex
[\fIGLOBAL\-FLAGS\fR]
\fICOMMAND\fR
[\fICOMMAND\-ARGS\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B nodex
is a local command\-line interface for inspecting and operating self\-hosted infrastructure.
It is Proxmox\-first, supporting both read\-only inspection and safe mutation operations across 31 provider capabilities with a five\-tier safety model.
Nodex is a single binary with no daemon, agent, or telemetry.
.SH GLOBAL FLAGS
.TP
.BI \-\-profile " " \fINAME\fR
Override the current profile.
.TP
.BI \-\-output " " \fIFORMAT\fR
Output format: \fBtable\fR, \fBjson\fR, or \fByaml\fR.
Default: table (TTY), json (non\-TTY).
.TP
.BI \-\-timeout " " \fIDURATION\fR
Request timeout (default: 30s).
.TP
.BI \-\-limit " " \fIN\fR
Limit output items (0 = no limit).
.TP
.B \-\-all
Aggregate across all configured profiles.
.TP
.B \-\-no\-color
Disable color output.
.TP
.B \-\-non\-interactive
Disable interactive prompts.
.TP
.B \-\-quiet
Suppress non\-essential output.
.TP
.B \-\-verbose
Info\-level stderr output.
.TP
.B \-\-debug
Debug\-level stderr output (redacted).
.SH MUTATION FLAGS
.TP
.B \-\-yes
Confirm reversible operations (Tier 1).
.TP
.B \-\-force
Confirm disruptive operations (Tier 2, requires \-\-yes).
.TP
.B \-\-wait
Wait for the provider task to complete before exiting.
.TP
.B \-\-expert
Enable expert\-mode operations (Tier 4: identity, ACL changes).
.TP
.B \-\-password\-stdin
Read password from stdin instead of interactive prompt.
.SH SAFETY TIERS
.TP
.B Tier 0 (Observation)
Read\-only. No confirmation required.
.TP
.B Tier 1 (Reversible)
Requires \-\-yes or interactive prompt.
.TP
.B Tier 2 (Disruptive)
Requires \-\-yes \-\-force or double confirmation.
.TP
.B Tier 3 (Destructive)
Requires typing the target identifier.
.TP
.B Tier 4 (Security Admin)
Requires \-\-expert flag.
.SH COMMANDS
.SS nodex init
Initialize nodex configuration interactively.
Non\-interactive with \-\-non\-interactive.
.SS nodex completion \fISHELL\fR
Generate shell completion (bash|zsh|fish). Writes to stdout.
.SS nodex version
Print version information.
.SS nodex provider list
List available providers.
.SS nodex provider capabilities \fINAME\fR
Show capabilities for a provider.
.SS nodex profile add \fINAME\fR [\-\-provider proxmox|pbs]
Add a new connection profile. The provider defaults to proxmox.
.SS nodex profile list
List all configured profiles.
.SS nodex profile show \fINAME\fR
Show details for a specific profile.
.SS nodex profile set\-credentials \fINAME\fR [\-\-backend file|keyring] [\-\-credential\-name \fINAME\fR]
Prompt for Proxmox API token credentials, store them, and update the profile credential reference.
.SS nodex profile use \fINAME\fR
Set the current active profile.
.SS nodex profile current
Show the current active profile.
.SS nodex profile test [\fINAME\fR]
Test connectivity for a profile.
.SS nodex profile remove \fINAME\fR [\-\-remove\-credential]
Remove a profile, optionally deleting its referenced credential.
.SS nodex profile export \fINAME\fR
Export a sanitized profile (no credentials). Writes JSON to stdout.
.SS nodex profile import
Import a profile from stdin.
.SS nodex node list
List all nodes.
.SS nodex node show \fINAME\fR
Show details for a specific node.
.SS nodex node status \fINAME\fR
Show detailed node status including CPU, memory, disk, and uptime.
.SS nodex node services \fINAME\fR
List services running on a node.
.SS nodex node network \fINAME\fR
